{"lemma": "تَحِيَّةٌ", "slug": "تَحِيَّةٌ", "root": "ح.#.#", "root_slug": "ح-_-_", "root_link": "/words/roots/ح-_-_", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "تَحِيَّة", "root": "حيي", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 6}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 2}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n9691"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "greeting", "fa": "سلام", "ur": "سلام", "tr": "selamlama", "id": "salam", "bn": "সলাম", "es": "saludo", "fr": "salut", "de": "Gruß", "ru": "приветствие", "zh": "问候"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of حَيَّا (ḥayyā) (form II)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a greeting"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n9691", "headword_ar": "تَحِيَّةٌ", "root": "HY: or HY and Hyw", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "inf. n. of 2. (Mgh, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A salutation,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "greeting,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A'Obeyd, AHeyth, Mgh, Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pronounced by one person to another on their meeting;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AHeyth;) particularly the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "salaAmN Ealayoka", "text_ar": "سَلَامٌ عَلَيْكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Mgh, * Msb;) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh;) the most comprehensive form thereof, used by the believer [to his fellow-believer], being the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~alaAmu Ealayokumo waraHomapu A@ll~`hi wabarakaAtuhu", "text_ar": "السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكُمْ وَرَحْمَةُ ا@للّٰهِ وَبَرَكَاتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (AHeyth:) hence it is pluralized; the pl. being"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taHiy~aAtN", "text_ar": "تَحِيَّاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taHaAyaA", "text_ar": "تَحَايَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Mgh.) ―         -b3-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Continuance,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "endurance;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "endless,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "everlasting, existence:"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 683}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, Msb, K, &c.:) and so it is said to mean in the following verse of Zuheyr Ibn-Jenáb ElKelbee; who was a [kind of] king among his people:"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "qado nilotuhu A_il~aA Alt~aHiy~aho \n                      \n                     \n                        walakul~u maA naAla AlfataY"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And indeed everything that the young man has attained, I have attained it, except endless existence"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: or, as some say, it here means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "security from death and from evils."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA. [But more probably the meaning is that next following: for in the Mz, 49th"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nwE", "text_ar": "نوع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", where this verse is cited, but with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino kul~i", "text_ar": "مِنْ كُلِّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the place of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "walakul~u", "text_ar": "وَلَكُلُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", he is said to have been (not a king, but,) “ a nobleman. ” See also, respecting him, p. x. of my Preface.]) And (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Dominion,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "kingship:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Fr, AA, S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.:) because the people of the Time of Ignorance used to greet kings [or rather those of Himyer] by the saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^abayota Al~aEona", "text_ar": "اَبَيْتَ الَّعْنَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which they addressed to none other than a king; so that when any one of them became a king, it was said of him,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN naAla Alt~aHiy~apa", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ نَالَ التَّحِيَّةَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one has attained the kingship"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Mgh: in which, and in the S, the foregoing verse is cited as an ex. of this last meaning.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alt~aHiy~aAtu lil~`hi", "text_ar": "التَّحِيَّاتُ لِلّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Endless existence belongs to God:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, Msb, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dominion,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "kingship:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, Yaakoob, S, Msb, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "freedom,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "security, from all evils,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Khálid Ibn-Yezeed, AHeyth,) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "from all causes of the cessation of existence:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AHeyth:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "endless existence, and security from evils, and dominion, and the like:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Fr:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the expressions"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of praise"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that indicate and imply the ascription of dominion and endless existence:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Kt:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "salutations and benedictions are Gods, and at his disposal."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh.) ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alt~aHiy~aAtu", "text_ar": "التَّحِيَّاتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also a term applied to the following form of words repeated in the ordinary prayers:"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alt~aHiy~aAtu lil~`hi waAlS~alawaAtu", "text_ar": "التَّحِيَّاتُ لِلّٰهِ وَالصَّلَوَاتُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAlT~ay~ibaAtu Als~alaAmu Ealayoka yaAA^ay~uhaA Aln~abiY~u waraHomapu A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "وَالطَّيِّبَاتُ السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكَ يَااَيُّهَا النَّبِىُّ وَرَحْمَةُ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wabarakaAtuhu Als~alaAmu EalayonaA waEalaY EibaAdi A@ll~`hi AlS~aAliHiyna", "text_ar": "وَبَرَكَاتُهُ السَّلَامُ عَلَيْنَا وَعَلَى عِبَادِ ا@للّٰهِ الصَّالِحِينَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$ohadu A^ano laA A_ilaAha A_il~aA A@ll~`hu waA^a$ohadu A^an~a muHam~adFA Eaboduhu", "text_ar": "اَشْهَدُ اَنْ لَا اـِلَاهَ اـِلَّا ا@للّٰهُ وَاَشْهَدُ اَنَّ مُحَمَّدًا عَبْدُهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "warasuwluhu", "text_ar": "وَرَسُولُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or (instead of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ebdh wrswlh", "text_ar": "عبده ورسوله"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rasuwlu A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "رَسُولُ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see 5 in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$hd", "text_ar": "شهد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b4-  The assigning to this word, as used in the Kur iv. 88, the meaning of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A gift"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a mistake. (Mgh.)       -A2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alt~aHaAyiY", "text_ar": "التَّحَايِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": ["AHeyth", "Lth", "Msb", "TA", "Fr", "Kt"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}